This LORA was trained on Uber Realistic Porn Merge (URPM) - Cunnilingus Edition (ALPHA)

This LORA is VERY specific. It only generates images of two women, (sometimes 3), performing cunnilingus on a woman lying on her back. It only works well at 512x512. I didn't do a lot of testing beyond that.

All sample images used Hi-Res fix @1.5 and ADetailer @768x768.

I didn't use any inpainting to demonstrate the model's consistency.

This LORA produces images that have better lighting and skin effects than URPM alone, but it lacks flexibility. It was trained using ~130 carefully manicured images of woman in a very specific pose, and that pose is what it does well, and really, the only thing it does.

For best results, you can use prompts such as:

a photo of two women on a bed licking pussy, cunnilingus, spread legs

or

a woman performs cunnilingus on a woman in a bed

or

a thousand permutations of this, as long as you use the above model, and the trigger word cunnilingus, you'll get results.

you can use "licking pussy" "eating pussy" "sucking pussy"

Pussy and Vagina are interchangeable.

I'm working on a more flexible lora, and a full model.

items.name: Transparent style
items.description:
My friend saw a photo in an article about SDXL and really liked the style. So they asked me to create this "LORA" with a transparent casing style. The concept is not very innovative, and the creation method is inspired by "konyconi." This is my poor imitation of their work, and anyone interested in this approach can give it a try. If you encounter any image distortion, please try adjusting the "LoRA Block Weight" or enlarging the image. When using it, please abide by local laws, refrain from harming others or engaging in illegal activities. If you have any ideas for improving this LORA, feel free to leave a comment.

제 친구가 SDXL 기사에서 보았던 사진의 스타일이 아주 마음에 들어서, 투명 외관 스타일의 "LORA"를 제작해달라고 부탁했습니다. 이 개념은 아주 새롭지는 않고, "konyconi"를 배워서 만들었습니다. 이것은 저의 서투른 모방으로, 이 방법에 관심이 있는 분들은 시도해볼 수 있습니다. 만약 화면 손상이 발생하면 "LoRA Block Weight"를 조정하거나 이미지를 확대해보십시오. 사용할 때에는 지역의 법률을 준수하고, 타인에게 해를 가하지 않고 불법 행위를 하지 않도록 주의하십시오. 이 LORA에 대한 개선 아이디어가 있다면, 댓글을 남겨주시기 바랍니다.

modelVersions.name: v1.20
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.4-1 like this: <lora:spiderPeoplev1.20:0.7>


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.description:
Old Al, as promised.

Be nice, have fun!

Alfredo James Pacino (/pəˈtʃiːnoʊ/ puh-CHEE-noh; Italian: [paˈtʃiːno]; born April 25, 1940) is an American actor. Considered one of the greatest and most influential actors of the 20th century, Pacino has received numerous accolades: including an Academy Award, two Tony Awards, and two Primetime Emmy Awards, making him one of the few performers to have achieved the Triple Crown of Acting. He has also been honored with the Cecil B. DeMille Award in 2001, the AFI Life Achievement Award in 2007, the National Medal of Arts in 2011, and the Kennedy Center Honors in 2016.[1][2][3][4]

A method actor, Pacino studied at HB Studio and the Actors Studio, where he was taught by Charlie Laughton and Lee Strasberg. Pacino went on to receive the Academy Award for Best Actor for his role in Scent of a Woman (1992). His other Oscar-nominated roles include The Godfather (1972), Serpico (1973), The Godfather Part II (1974), Dog Day Afternoon (1975), and ...And Justice for All (1979), Dick Tracy (1990), Glengarry Glen Ross (1992), and The Irishman (2019). Other notable films include The Panic in Needle Park (1971), Author! Author! (1982), Scarface (1983), The Godfather Part III (1990), Carlito's Way (1993), Heat (1995), Donnie Brasco (1997), The Devil's Advocate (1997), Any Given Sunday (1999), The Insider (1999), Insomnia (2002), Ocean's Thirteen (2007), Jack and Jill (2011), Once Upon a Time in Hollywood (2019) and House of Gucci (2021).

On television, Pacino has acted in several productions for HBO, including Angels in America (2003) and the Jack Kevorkian biopic You Don't Know Jack (2010), winning a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Miniseries or a Movie for each. Pacino starred in the Amazon Video series Hunters (2020–2023). He has also had an extensive career on stage. He is a two-time Tony Award winner, winning Best Featured Actor in a Play in Does a Tiger Wear a Necktie? (1969) and Best Actor in a Play for The Basic Training of Pavlo Hummel (1977).

Pacino made his directing debut with the documentary Looking for Richard (1996); Pacino had played the lead role on stage in 1977. He has also acted as Shylock in a 2004 feature film adaptation and 2010 stage production of The Merchant of Venice. Pacino directed and starred in Chinese Coffee (2000), Wilde Salomé (2011), and Salomé (2013). Since 1994, he has been the joint president of the Actors Studio.

items.name: Sarah Miller - The Last of Us
items.description:
Good day folks,

I'm here to present my initial work on creating a LoRA model for stable diffusion, focusing on Sarah Miller, a character from the video game "The Last of Us".

Who is Sarah Miller ?

Sarah Miller is a character from the video game "The Last of Us", developed by Naughty Dog. She is the 12-year-old daughter of the game's protagonist, Joel. Sarah appears in the early stages of the game.

How to use

In all versions is it possible to change the age of the character, ( example here ) so please specify the correct age in the prompt.

It should also be possible to change various physical aspects, such as length and color of hair, eye color etc ... so be specific in the prompt if the result does not correspond to your expectations.

The prompt suggested to have a character as similar as possible to the one in the video game

1girl, Sara Miller, 12 years old, blonde, short hairs, blue eyes, bracelet, necklaces, wearing pajamas, double long sleeves, long pants,

Sometimes it is necessary to add

double long sleeves, sleeves

to the negative prompt to remove some artifacts

SD1.5 v1.0

This is my first foray into this kind of work for stable diffusion 1.5, and I'm aware of the challenges and the steep learning curve involved. A significant hurdle was the limited amount of visual references available for the character, which added complexity to the task. While I am conscious that the current model may not be up to the mark, I consider this as a stepping stone towards better and more accurate models. I am committed to continuously improving and refining this model, and I'm looking forward to sharing updated versions in the future. I appreciate your understanding and support as I navigate this new territory.

It only works with Stable Diffusion 1.5 and all derived models (which are most of the ones available here on Civitai)

SD1.5 v2.3

Improved version of v1.0.

Lots of work still needs to be done to achieve a good result.

It only works with Stable Diffusion 1.5 and all derived models (which are most of the ones available here on Civitai)

SDXL v1.0

Much better version of v1.0 for stable diffusion 1.5 thanks to the capabilities of Stable Diffusion XL

It only works with Stable Diffusion XL and all derived models

SDXL v3.0

slightly improved version with the addition of images with better quality

It only works with Stable Diffusion XL and all derived models

SDXL v3.1 ( 80 epochs version of SDXLv3.0 )

This is the same training batch of SDXLv3.0, but with a much higher epoch ( v3.0 is 18 epochs v3.1 is 80 epochs ).

Suggested weight: 0.8

It only works with Stable Diffusion XL and all derived models

Future releases for stable diffusion 1.5?

Yes, I'm working on a improved version of v1.0. You can see the firsts results here

Dataset source ?

You can download the dataset of images used to train the models here ( sd1.5 versions ) and here ( SDXL versions )

items.name: d3caricature
items.description:
Do you want to create characters with big ears, low forehead, prominent nose and exaggerated facial expression? You got it, that's what d3caricature aims to create!

This is my first attempt at creating an embedding (long live Textual Inversion!) for Stable Diffusion, and during a steep learning curve over the last month or so this is the result.

Works with "vanilla" Stable Diffusion 2.1 768, but also with a multitude of other 2.1 models. Does not affect animals (much), only people, and will also create quite extreme results in many cases.

***

Therefor I have included three versions of this embedding:

d3caricature-beta-x - a 1 vector evenly distributed version (lowest impact)
d3caricature-beta-y - a 6 vector "half weight" evenly distributed version (medium impact)
d3caricature-beta-z - a 6 vector full-on evenly distributed version (high impact)

Experiment by using them at the beginning of the prompt, in the middle, or at the end, with higher or lower weights, or higher/lower CFG.

They have been thoroughly tested with stable-diffusion-2.1-768, but I highly recommend using them with other 2.1 models such as perpetualDiffusion10_v10Moon (and sun) and illuminatiDiffusionV1_v11.

***

All versions of the embedding is based on the same training set of 68 hand picked and fine-tuned images, in the training course of:

  • 500 steps @ lr 0.375-0.5 (linear with warmup)

  • 1000 steps @ lr 0.075-0.1 (linear with warmup)

  • 1000 steps @ lr 0.015-0.02 (linear with warmup)

  • 2000 steps @ lr 0.003-0.004 (linear)

  • 2500 steps @ lr 0.0006-0.0008 (linear)

  • 2500 steps @ lr 0.00016

All training done with 4 gradient_accumulation_steps, in invokeai 2.3.5, and then combined using a1111 with the Embedding Inspector extension.

***

I really do hope that you find this embedding useful and that you have loads of fun with it! This embedding is in beta state, but I have no idea if it will ever reach a "release candidate" state, nor will I even expect it to do so.

It was created simply because I had an idea that I could not let go of and just had to create ;)

Thank you, and enjoy!
Much love

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: MODILL PASTELL - Modern Style Illustration LoRa
items.description:
MODILL PASTELL - Modern Style Illustration LoRa

This LoRa the more "pastel/detailed" one. Still my biggest LoRa yet, ~500 images for a bit less than 50000 steps x2 (I trained it two times with different settings and merged the results) and then carefully merged with other unpublished LoRa of mine. As like the other, Its dataset contains mainly modern style illustration+the dataset prevoiusly used for CoolKids LoRa and the datasets for the others LoRa I mixed in. It should be more flexible (especially at adults themed images) and it should work on a wide variety of subjects.

!!! IMPORTANT - READ BEFORE LEAVING REVIEWS, PLEASE !!!

In the example images the weights are not present since the LoRa was applied using the additional network plugin in A1111 instead of the native LoRa extension. Below are the suggested weights, tune them until your images comes out without distortions!

Use it at ~0.3 weight if you use it on a illustration like checkpoints (Dreamshaper is a good example) for a digital illustration look

Use it at ~0.45 up to 0.6 weight if you use it on a realistic like checkpoints (Realistic Vision is a good example) for a pastell illustration look

I also found that using the word "whimsical" yeld pretty good results, consider incorporating that into your prompts

Training LoRa necessitate a lot of coffee. If you think that what I do is useful and want to help me keep doing this you can buy me a coffe here: https://ko-fi.com/clumsy_trainer

items.name: Sitting handjob
items.description:
LoRA trained to generate 2 characters side by side (mainly sitting) performing a handjob.

This one was tough to make it work, and it is still not as effective and consistent as I'd like to. It will take more work to get a nice output.

But I tried various datasets, captions and training parameters, and this was the best result. It generates penises on girls sometimes (even if there weren't any in the dataset); if you're into that, you're in for a treat. Adding male-related tags can help to counter that.

Please rate and leave a like if you enjoyed it! And be sure to follow to check out the upcoming models.

Recommended prompt: 1girl, 1boy, sitting, handjob, couple

In general, I recommend using the complete prompt above, or increase the LoRA's weight beyond 1.0, to get better results. The reason to use couple is that it works better generating 2 characters in portrait aspect ratios like 512x768. All aspect ratios should be able to generate results.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content! I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: Nradiowave Androids [We Can Rebuild Her Edition]
items.description:
Makes android girls in style inspiration from nradiowave.

How to use
The core tag is "1girl" along with "android", beyond that you can use "mechanical arms", "mechanical legs" and "robot joints" to refine the look further.
Many images had android girls in various states of damage from the artists one-shots so you can put "damaged" and "amputee" as either positive or negative tags depending on what you're trying to prompt.
Most of the images were of sketch quality so LoRA performance isn't quite as good as I'd like, particularly eyes tend to come out blank. You can avoid this by specifically prompting eyes, adding "smile" or anything other face emotion should help too.
Alternatively, you can just skip it if you're going for the dead-eyed shut-down android theme.
For more tips on what to prompt please see the sample images or uploaded zip of training tags.

MISC
Trained on NAI at 512 res with a dataset of 82 images.
All images except the semi-realistic one are, slightly cherrypicked, raw txt2img upscaled without any inpainting or helper embeddings.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the artist. Go support them if you want the good stuff.
